  "doc_id": "5806",
  "text": "A further layer of complexity surrounds RA regulation of Th-cell fate with bi-phasic effects of RA on Th1 and Th2 differentiation reported in vitro [CITATION_1] . In Th1 differentiation, induction of T-bet is dependent on IFN-γ-Stat1 signaling whereas maintenance of T-bet expression is dependent on IL12-Stat4 activation [CITATION_2] , suggesting distinct roles for RA in the regulation of these signaling pathways. Similarly, a bi-phasic model for Th17 differentiation is emerging with early commitment dependent on TGF-β and IL-6 signaling but maintenance and stability dependent on IL-21 and IL-23 signaling [CITATION_3] . Animal models which allow temporal control of RA signaling will be invaluable for dissecting out the role of RA in early vs. late phase differentiation.",
